metadata.name: Chek le Rat
metadata.description:
Once there was a graffiti artist rat named Chek le Rat, who lived in the streets of Paris. Growing up, Chek watched his parents create art and leave a mark on the world. and it was no surprise since his parents were the famous street artist Banksy.  It was something that inspired him to become an artist as well, and he had always dreamed of making a name for himself in the street art community. He is known for his unique and striking stencils of rats and urban animals that he put around the city. Chek had always been fascinated by the world of social media, and he had a dream of being verified on Twitter by one of the most well-known tech icons, Elon Musk.

One day, Chek heard that Elon Musk was in Paris for a business meeting. Determined to make his dream a reality, Chek decided to take action. He gathered all of his best stencils and set out to find Musk.
